      <h2>Lebanon's Monetary Values Drop</h2>
      <img src="assets/news.jpg" alt="Lebanon's Currency" class="w-50">
      <p>Lebanon's currency, the Lebanese pound, has been dropping in value rapidly due to the country's economic crisis. In recent months, the value of the pound has fallen by over 90% against the US dollar, leading to a surge in prices for basic goods and services.</p>
      <h3>Impact on Citizens</h3>
      <p>The devaluation of the pound has had a significant impact on the lives of Lebanese citizens. Many have seen their savings wiped out and struggle to afford basic necessities like food and medicine. Unemployment rates have skyrocketed as businesses struggle to stay afloat in the economic downturn.</p>
      <h3>Government Response</h3>
      <p>The Lebanese government has been criticized for its handling of the economic crisis. Despite promises to implement reforms and secure international aid, little progress has been made towards stabilizing the currency and improving the economy.</p>
      <p>Stay tuned for more updates on Lebanon's monetary values and the ongoing economic crisis.</p>
